      "content": "I see what you're saying about the moral aspect, but you seem to be dismissing the strategic side pretty quickly. If a policy triggers a decade of civil war and prevents any chance of regional stability, how can a geopolitical analyst call that a \"success\"? It feels like you're prioritizing a moral framework over the actual measurable outcomes of the policy itself.",
